Job Description:
The primary responsibility for the Sr. Data Engineer / Tech Lead is to ensure data accessibility, quality, and reliability within the client's data platform ecosystem.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Design and develop end-to-end data pipelines and ETL processes using Snowflake, Denodo, DBT Cloud, Fivetran, and AWS Glue, ensuring seamless data integration, transformation, and loading.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather data requirements and implement scalable data models and schemas within Snowflake and Denodo, ensuring optimal performance and data consistency.
Implement and maintain data orchestration workflows using Stonebranch, ensuring efficient and reliable scheduling and automation of data processes.
Work with EnterpriseDataLake for ingestion and storage of data from various sources, ensuring the availability and accessibility of data for analytics and reporting purposes.
Utilize Azure DevOps and Teraform to implement and manage infrastructure as code, ensuring streamlined deployment and scalability of data engineering solutions.

The Alaska Native Tribal Health Consortium is a non-profit Tribal health organization designed to meet the unique health needs of Alaska Native and American Indian people living in Alaska. In partnership with the more than 171,000 Alaska Native and American Indian people that we serve and the Tribal health organizations of the Alaska Tribal Health System, ANTHC provides world-class health services, which include comprehensive medical services at the Alaska Native Medical Center, wellness programs, disease research and prevention, rural provider training and rural water and sanitation systems construction.

The Refining Value Chain Optimization group at the Kenai Refinery is seeking candidates for an opening in the RVCO Economics and Planning Group. The RVCO E&P Team is responsible for optimizing refinery operations, developing short- and long-range production forecasts, feedstock scheduling, product production and scheduling, project analysis, and intermediate inventory management. All members of the team are expected to be actively engaged in ensuring all products meet specifications. The successful candidate will have an opportunity to interact with and influence many areas of the company. The group works closely with Operations and Technical Services to understand unit constraints and communicate the economic drivers of each of the operating areas. The team also works directly with Global Feedstock and Clean Product Value Chains, RVCO Findlay/SATX, and Product Quality to evaluate opportunities on feedstocks, products, and inter-refinery transfers.

RESPONSIBILITIES
The candidate will initially be trained to use the refinery linear program (PIMS) and APS. After mastering the linear program the individual is expected to serve as the short-term forecaster. Responsibilities of the position include:
Issue one to two month forecast on a weekly basis. Review unit and tank farm constraints, market prices, product demands, and feedstock availability as a part of the forecast process.
Work with Tech Service and Operations to identify and optimize around unit constraints.
Explain forecast variances, evaluate feedstock and product opportunities, and run sensitivities as needed.
Provide incremental economics on a weekly basis to support optimization efforts within the refinery.
Perform ad hoc analysis to guide business decisions around outages and slow downs.
Analyze capital project value and provide transparent economics.
Provide coverage for other responsibilities in the group, examples include blending, modeling, target tracking, etc…

EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE
Degree: Bachelor of Science
Major Discipline: Chemical Engineering or other Technical Discipline
Years’ Experience Required: A minimum of 4 years Refinery process experience is preferred
Refinery Linear Programming/Economic Analysis Tools i.e (PIMS) experience is preferred
Travel Required: minimum
*** This position is part of a job family with multiple grade levels. The successful candidate will be placed at a level commensurate with experience and qualifications.***
If selected candidate dose not hold an engineering degree they will be placed in a appropriate job family.
